 First, note that the expression inside the absolute value sign, namely $x$, will always be positive, so we can take its cube without changing its sign. Thus,
\begin{align*}
x\clubsuit y=|x|^3+y&=8+y\qquad\textrm{when}\,\,x=2\\
&=\boxed{10}
\end{align*}
